	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />SNES can normally trasfer a bit less than 6K of data into VRAM in a normal VBlank via DMA. When rendering is turned off, SNES can transfer about 45K per frame. Since 8bpp seems to be a must for the 'Super NES', 256*200 would be ~51K, i.e. more than SNES is capable to do with disabled rendering.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


